modules.description: Provides atomic read, write, and delete operations on a hash table indexed by integers, using thread-local storage to manage state. Operates on key-value pairs where keys are integers and values are arbitrary OCaml values. Used to track per-thread data in concurrent applications without synchronization during lookups.

Provides operations to create, query, and modify a hash table indexed by integers, supporting thread-safe access within a single domain. Works with a generic value type and ensures bindings are updated without locks. Used to track per-thread state in concurrent applications where threads share a common domain.
